  "instructions": [
    "In a large bowl, whisk together soy sauce, gochujang, honey, rice vinegar, Gochugaru, and cocoa powder. Add the chicken and marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Remove the chicken from the marinade and bake for 20-25 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "While the chicken is cooking, combine the gochujang sauce, honey, and rice vinegar in a small saucepan. Whisk over medium heat until the sauce is smooth and hot.",
    "To assemble the bowls, place a portion of cooked chicken on each plate. Spoon the gochujang sauce over the top, followed by a sprinkle of toasted sesame seeds and green onions.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
